Available to the open market for the first time since its completion in 2009, is 400 King William Street Adelaide and in particular the whole of level 9.

Being one of Adelaide’s largest floorplates and with natural light from all four sides, 400 King William Street is an exceptional opportunity in today’s tightening A grade marketplace.

Available from January 2022 onwards, the whole floor of 2,036 square metres is fully fitted and provides an efficient and flexible working environment. 

The End of Trip Facilities in the basement are first class and including showers, free towel service, 350 lockers and space for 80 bicycles along with a wellness centre designed by Fauna Yoga that provides the tenants with the ability to book yoga, meditation and pilates rooms.

The building was designed to ensure maximum energy performance, recently achieving a 5.5 Star NABERS rating.

Please contact the exclusive agents to inspect this opportunity

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: FANTASTIC SPACE AVAILABLE IN RUNDLE MALL

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Myer Centre Adelaide is one of Adelaide's most iconic buildings and the largest shopping centre in the CBD, comprising 60,109 sqm of retail accommodation,  SA's biggest Myer department store,  Rundle Mall's largest food court and over 79 specialty retailers.

Holding a prominent position on Rundle Mall, Adelaide's main shopping destination the Centre also benefits from North Terrace entrances connecting the Centre with Adelaide's cultural & tourism institutions, Universities and the River Bank precinct  and  underground parking for 467 cars.

Purchased recently by Starhill Global REIT,  the centre has recently undergone a $35 million upgrade including a complete refurbishment of Myer's tenancy, which is located over 4 floors of the centre. National retailers within the centre include fashion brands such as NineWest, Review, Aquila, Platypus Shoes and Honey Birdette. Other national retailers include Lush, Sunglass Hut, Thomas Sabo and Angus & Coote with mini majors including Rebel Sport, Priceline and Toyworld.

Predominantly showcasing fashion brands from Rundle Mall upwards, the basement level  hosts both a 'Food Underground' dining  and health & beauty precinct, with tenants that include McDonalds, KFC, Gloria Jeans, Boost, Chemist Warehouse and Priceline.

Opportunities now exist within the Centre and Food Underground. For all leasing enquiries please contact Samuel Miettunen 0450 438 874
